What I used in the Viet Nam seminar were bibliographies prepared by Dr. Edwin Moise at Clemson University....his may be the most comprehensive.  Check him out at the following website:<br><br>
http://hubcap.clemson.edu/~eemoise/bibliography.html/<br><br>
John, once you finish working on the literature, poetry, music, etc..... will you put your bibliography on line? It would be great to use -- or refer to -- next year when I again teach the Vietnam seminar.<br><br>
I am working on an expanded chronology of the war-era, using copies from the New York Times annual index. I've got a good handle on events from the mid 1930's through 1959.... and still I'm pushing ahead. To my left on the table next to my computer is a pile 6 inches thick of these annual index references to articles in the NYT from 1960-1975...... I will work on this little by little over the summer and would hope to have something available on the web by Fall.<br><br>
When YOU use a chronology for your class, what one/source do you use? Simplified, detailed?<br><br>
Regards.
